a graphic shell that executes sh commands based on user selection 

purpose: for the demo scenario, to support app launch from display and gamehat
(/dev/events), whereas "sh" only supports uart console which demo lacks 

feature: 
- can interpret a line of shell commands (not only supports launch of a
single program (as in NJU OS menu))
- read from a config file (optional)

dependency: 
libc(newlib),libminisdl, /dev/events, usbkb or gamehat 

reference: 
NJU OS menu
https://github.com/NJU-ProjectN/navy-apps/blob/master/apps/menu/menu.cpp


